soap opera</link> <it><opera wordnetid="107026352" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../990/341990.xml">
One Life to Live</link></opera>
</it>, and was cast as the teenage son of <link>
Michael Goodwin</link> and <person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../835/2574835.xml">
Leigh Taylor-Young</link></actor>
</person>
 on the 1983 prime time serial <it><event wordnetid="100029378" confidence="0.8">
<social_event wordnetid="107288639" confidence="0.8">
<show wordnetid="106619065" confidence="0.8">
<psychological_feature wordnetid="100023100" confidence="0.8">
<attraction wordnetid="106615561" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../044/142044.xml">
The Hamptons</link></attraction>
</psychological_feature>
</show>
</social_event>
</event>
</it>. His earliest starring assignment in films was as the best friend of troubled teenager <screenwriter wordnetid="110564400" confidence="0.9173553029164789">
<actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
